Completed slice:
- 2026-05-13: Added crate-level unit test structure checks, complete syntax fixture gates, and snapshot review workflow for testing-policy progress.

Implementation decisions:
- Unit-test structure is enforced per workspace crate by `scripts/check-unit-test-structure.sh`.
- Golden `.lqs` and `.lgl` fixtures are treated as complete valid programs; diagnostic fragments must live under `tests/fixtures/invalid`.
- Snapshot review uses `scripts/review-snapshots.sh --check` in CI and `scripts/review-snapshots.sh review` with `cargo-insta` installed for interactive review.
- Near-limit source files remain split-required before future growth: `crates/linguini-syntax/src/lib.rs`, `crates/linguini-syntax/src/lexer.rs`, `crates/linguini-syntax/src/parser/locale_parser.rs`, and `crates/linguini-cldr/src/data.rs`.

